AVIAN INFLUENZA (71) - CAMBODIA (KAMPONG CHAM): OIE
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 12 Apr 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, WAHID Vol. 20 [19 Apr 2007] - No. 16 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>

Highly pathogenic avian influenza, Cambodia
-----------------------------------------------
Information received on 12 Apr 2007 from Mr. Sen Sovann, Deputy
Director, Department of Animal Health and Production, Ministry of
Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Phnom Penh, Cambodia:
Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date 6 Apr 2007
Date of confirmation of event 10 Apr 2007
Report date 12 Apr 2007
Date submitted to OIE 12 Apr 2007
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence 5 Sep 2006
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Highly pathogenic avian influenza virus
Serotype H5N1
Nature of diagnosis: Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (advanced)
Report pertains to: Entire country
New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 Laork, Kreak, Ponhea Kreak, Kg Cham
Date of start of outbreak 6 Apr 2007
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not submitted)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Species Birds
Susceptible 1086
Cases 302
Deaths 302
Destroyed 784
Slaughtered 0
Affected population backyard poultry (chickens and ducks) in one
village (5 households)
Summary of outbreaks Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak statistics
Species Birds
Apparent morbidity rate 27.81 percent
Apparent mortality rate 27.81 percent
Apparent case fatality rate 100.00 percent
Proportion susceptible removed* 100.00 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction or slaughter
Epidemiology
Source of infection: Unknown or inconclusive; Under investigation
Epidemiological comments Stamping out was undertaken on 11 Apr 2007.
Surveillance in the villages around the outbreak is ongoing.
Laboratory name and type: Pasteur Institute, Cambodia (Regional
Reference Laboratory)
Species Birds
Test reverse transcription - polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR)
Test date 10 Apr 2007
Result Positive
Species Birds
Test pathogen isolation by egg inoculation
Test date 10 Apr 2007
Result Positive Species
Laboratory name and type: National Animal Health and Production
Investigation Center (NAHPIC) (National laboratory)
Species Birds
Test pathogen isolation by egg inoculation
Test date 7 Apr 2007
Result Positive
Species Birds
Test reverse transcription - polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR)
Test date 7 Apr 2007
Result Positive
